<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{mou}}}} means "already" and when combined with a verb in the past tense
the meaning is that the action specified by the verb has been completed.
</p>

<p>
In an affirmative interrogative sentence @HI{{@EM{{mou}}}} means "yet" or "already".
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
In a negative sentence @HI{{@EM{{mou}}}} means "not yet" or "not any longer".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@EM{{mou}}@KJ{{sake}}wo@KJ{{drink}}masenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I won't drink <em>sake</em> any more.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
A postive answer to the question @HI{{@EM{{mou}}}}@Vmasustem{{}}@HI{{mashitaka}} indicates that the requested action has been performed.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mou@KJ{{baggage^thing}}wo@KJ{{send*off}}rimashitaka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Have you sent the parcel yet?
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{hai,@KJ{{send*off}}rimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yes I have.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<p>

<p>
A negative answer to the same question would be to say "not yet".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mou@KJ{{baggage^thing}}wo@KJ{{send*off}}rimashitaka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Have you sent the parcel yet?
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{iie,madadesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      No, not yet.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
An answer of the form @HI{{iie,}}@Vmasustem{{}}@HI{{masendeshita}} would imply that the task was not performed
rather than it has <em>not yet</em> been performed.
</p>

